##The insurance industry is off to a flying start: Why fewer people are insured in an epidemic

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to clear the fog, to seek the truth, to watch the Times.

Under the new crown pneumonia epidemic, the mainstream insurance enterprise falls into the premium decline crisis

Affected by the epidemic, the March 15 evening party was postponed, but the voice of consumer rights protection will not be postponed. Insurance products are still a hot topic of complaint and rights protection. According to statistics from the China Consumer Association, 594 complaints involving automobile insurance categories were filed in 2019, bundling car insurance and inducing consumer insurance loans has become a hot spot for complaints, around March 15 this year, around the insurance products of the outcry set off a new upsurge.

It is worth noting that this year has not been easy for the insurance industry. Pingan, PICC, China Life, China Pacific Insurance and Xinhua insurance all recently reported premium income in January and February this year, total premium income in the first two months was 671.974 billion yuan, up 4.3 percent year-on-year, while total premium income in February was 143.539 billion yuan, down 72.8 percent month-on-month.

Consumer Insurance Rights Still, the new crown pneumonia epidemic in the insurance market will have what kind of expectations?

Red Flag on the door

Red Is the traditional insurance sales season, most insurance companies will start red as the focus of the year, in order to complete premium income, focused on the launch of preferential insurance products. Premium income in the first quarter, especially in January and February, often accounts for a large proportion of annual premiums.

However, this year's hot insurance sales season has been generally cold. The data released so far show that in the first two months of this year, the top five listed insurance companies, China Life Insurance premium income 228 billion yuan, up 20.5% year-on-year; China Pacific Insurance premium income 90.923 billion yuan, iNSURANCE PREMIUM INCOME OF XINHUA was 39.56 billion yuan, up 44.2 percent year on year; that of Chinese people was 124.161 billion yuan, down 5.13 percent year on year; that of Pingan was 189.33 billion yuan, down 8.6 percent year on year. Premiums for three of the five listed insurers rose, while two slipped.

In February, the top five listed insurers saw a sharp drop in premium income month-on-month.

China life's premium income was 34.5 billion yuan, down 82.2 percent from the previous month; China Pacific Insurance's was 21.306 billion yuan, down 69.4 percent from the previous month; Xinhua's was 8.855 billion yuan, down 71.2 percent from the previous month; and Chinese People's premium income was 32.304 billion yuan, pINGAN's premium income was 46.574 billion yuan, down 67.4% month on month.

Premium income of listed insurance enterprises in January and February

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A large insurance company in Beijing told China News weekly that the absence of the insurance industry's successful start this year was mainly affected by the new crown epidemic, which broke out during the Spring Festival, causing the insurance companies themselves to face delays in resuming work and blocking the sales channels of products such as bank insurance, the traditional car market downturn, such as property and insurance income dropped sharply.

According to industry analysis, insurance premiums of insurance companies dropped sharply in February this year, which was expected. February was the outbreak period of the domestic epidemic. The whole country was closed to the outside world to fight the epidemic. Home Isolation and online work made insurance companies suffer the biggest impact, add in the extension of the Lunar New Year holiday in February, it is not surprising that premium income of insurance companies has fallen sharply.

According to analysts from brokerage firms, in the medium to long term, the new pneumonia outbreak has raised consumers'awareness of self-protection against disease and protection against health risks, and helped stimulate the need for health insurance allocation. After the outbreak ended, demand for insurance is set to rebound, which is expected to drive the industry's rapid growth.

According to normal logic, every major epidemic or disaster will raise consumers'awareness of insurance. The market expects the insurance industry's revenue to rise substantially. However, under the new pneumonia epidemic situation, the mainstream insurance enterprise but simultaneously falls into the premium decline crisis.

China News Week also found that the slowdown in sales during the insurance industry's boom period was not the first of its kind this year.

In 2018, due to the influence of the former China Insurance Regulatory Commission to strengthen the supervision of insurance products and sales, especially article 134 to strengthen the supervision of Quick Return Insurance Products, omnipotent and all-round insurance products were suspended, and Article 136 to demand strict investigation against misleading sales of insurance, the insurance industry, which has experienced three consecutive years of high premium growth, began to experience a cold start, with the industry's premium income showing negative growth in the first quarter. For 2018 as a whole, the original premium income of the insurance industry as a whole only increased by 3.92% year-on-year, hitting a seven-year low.

In 2019, the life insurance market was the first to freeze. In January of that year, Pingan, China Pacific Insurance and China Taiping's life insurance premiums rose only 5.22% , 2.89% and 9.58% respectively from a year earlier, ending three consecutive years of double-digit growth, through the opening season without the festive red.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Trends of listed life insurance business

In 2020, China's insurance industry is facing unprecedented pressure.

The analysis points out that on the underwriting end, the traditional offline sales channels are blocked, agents are falling off, and it is difficult for insurance companies to increase their staff, which directly affects the growth of new orders, and the delay in the resumption of work by enterprises, resulting in different degrees of impact on the banking and Group Insurance Channels; on the Investment End, the Federal Reserve has cut interest rates twice in a row or triggered a global low interest rate environment. The Central Bank of China is expected to cut interest rates again. The scope and intensity of global interest rate cuts this year have been further expanded, and asset scarcity and credit risks have risen, put pressure on the investment of Insurance Funds.

Some News said that at present some insurance companies mature assets yield has been inverted phenomenon, this year's new investment assets yield less than 5% , significantly lower than last year's yield level.

Data for the first two months of this year also showed that the premiums for new orders in the life insurance bank insurance market fell by more than 40% year-on-year, including a 69% year-on-year decline for new orders in February and a seven-year low for new orders. In the property insurance market, individual premiums of PICC, China Pacific Insurance and Pingan all recorded negative growth in February, at-6.8 per cent,-10.8 per cent and-7.9 per cent respectively.

Red Door Cold, new single negative growth, property insurance business contraction and other problems of the future performance of the insurance industry?

However, there are industry voices that the insurance industry by adjusting the allocation of assets, increase insurance business resilience and other ways, can largely withstand the adverse impact. The current insurance stock price has reflected a variety of adverse factors, for investors, it is a good opportunity for long-term allocation. After the epidemic is over, the insurance industry is expected to see a bounce in earnings and share prices.

Circumventing the security mess

Inconsistent with the chill in premium sales, irregularities in the insurance industry are on the rise.

According to preliminary statistics from China News weekly, the official website of the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission (CBRC) in January issued two administrative punishment decisions against the insurance industry, with fines of 750,000 yuan and 248 issued by local regulatory authorities, with fines of 47.086 million yuan.

In January alone, the National Insurance Regulatory Authority issued a total of 250 tickets, up 320.5 percent year-on-year, and the total amount of fines was 47.836 million yuan, up 304.2 percent year-on-year. The 45 insurance intermediaries were fined a total of 5.665 million yuan (excluding individual penalties) , and 33 insurance companies were fined a total of 34.26 million yuan (excluding individual penalties) , an increase of 15 from the same period last year, pICC, Cheonan and Pingan ranked in the top three with fines of 6.75 million yuan, 5.41 million yuan and 2.6 million yuan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The punishment decision recently announced by the CBRC

Preliminary statistics show that in the first two months of this year, China's insurance regulator issued a total of 289 insurance fines, compared with 167 in the first two months of 2019, with a total fine of 26.09 million yuan. In terms of fines, property and casualty insurance remained the largest area of violations by insurance companies, with 15 of the 33 companies penalized in January and 8 of the 13 companies penalized in February.

The non-compliance items include, the problems of false data, false propaganda and misleading consumers, the problems of collecting fees from fictitious insurance intermediary business, the problems of illegal operation of intermediary institutions, the problems of internal risk management loopholes, illegal return on profits and other insurance violations are all involved.

For example, PICC property insurance, Tian 'an property insurance and Dadi property insurance were fined for "using insurance intermediary companies to draw up insurance intermediary business cover fees and preparing and providing false statement data" . Staff at the Suizhou branch of Huatai Life Insurance Company were fined for deceiving policyholders with false information after they posted a "hunger" marketing campaign on Wechat. Sunshine life submitted to the supervision of the statement did not truthfully fill out the "end of the number of marketers" , internal control is not strict, risk management system is not sound penalty. China Construction Bank Nanchang Branch fined for loan compulsory tying-in insurance products.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sunshine Life Insurance is penalized

After two years of "strict supervision" in 2017 and 2018, letters of supervision, the number of fines and the amount of fines have all been reduced in 2019. This shows that the insurance industry has been put under control after its rectification, but the number of violations has risen again in 2020.

Analysts said the insurance industry will not relax strict regulation, the increase in fines means instead that "strict regulation" will become the norm.

China Pacific Insurance experts said the outbreak has accelerated the industry's "red-hot" transformation and upgrading, which is both a healthy development of the insurance industry's historical opportunities, but also allows consumers to get more real insurance products in the future. Under the epidemic situation, risk enterprises are generally aware of the importance and urgency of digital transformation, and efficient online channels will be one of the keys to future competition.

However, the Internet insurance regulation is still in a blind area and relevant regulations are still being improved. On October 10,2019, the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission issued the notice of the General Office of the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission on the rectification of the disorder of Bank Insurance Institutions Infringing upon the rights and interests of consumers, which directly refers to the series of disorder of Internet insurance infringing upon the rights and interests of consumers.

The Internet insurance sales to insurance product key information description is not sufficient, not clear, such as propaganda deliberately use misleading words combination, confusion and Ambiguity Insurance Liability; Internet business important information disclosure, risk tips, customer notice is not standard, clear, such as sales page or insurance coverage is not complete, important content does not take font, color and other special tips; The process of insurance is embedded in other business processes such as network borrowing, but the amount of insurance, premium, insurance liability, insurance products and other underwriters are not informed enough.

In the online sales, the right of free choice of consumers is restricted, such as cooperating with the third party online lending platform, forcing consumers to take out accident insurance and guarantee insurance in the process of borrowing. The roles and positioning boundaries of Insurance Companies, intermediary agencies and third-party network platforms in internet business are not clear, and the operating entities of third-party network platforms are not consistent with those of third-party network platforms that disclose cooperation, there is a risk of illegal operation.

Online claims management is not in place, consumers online insurance claims after no reply and waiting for a long time, online and offline claims service in place. Third-party network platform through the sale of insurance, dispute disputes, sales platform and insurance companies buck each other, deal with the statute of limitations is long. Insurance Companies and insurance intermediary organizations have not kept the insurance information, operation track, operation time, and the time when the insurance company receives the application for Insurance.

In December 2019, the Internet Insurance Business Regulation Consultation Draft, which was drafted under the leadership of the China Banking Regulatory Commission, is soliciting views from the industry, and it is believed that a new Internet insurance regulatory system will be introduced soon, internet insurance regulation will be brought into the strict regulatory orbit, insurance companies are also facing strict regulation on the transformation line.

Epidemic Storm, and you and I live closely related to the booming insurance industry, whether the chaos, the achievement of great success?
